**************************
Not So Simple Backup Suite
**************************

Installation Instructions
=========================

Prerequist
==========
python (>=2.5)
pygnome
pyglade
pynotify
fuse
python-pexpect
sshfs (for ssh plugin)
curlftpfs (for ftp and sftp plugins)
gettext
python-setuptools
pyGTK (>= 2.10)

* On Ubuntu:
  sudo apt-get install python-notify fuse-utils python-gnome python-glade\
                       python-gtk

Easy way
========

* If you use Debian or Ubuntu, try apt-get:
 * Install the nssbackup team repository 
  * deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/nssbackup-team/ubuntu intrepid main
  * deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/nssbackup-team/ubuntu hardy main
  * deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/nssbackup-team/ubuntu gutsy main
 * sudo apt-get install nssbackup

 [Note] See the PPA page for the full list of repository:
        https://launchpad.net/~nssbackup-team/+archive/ppa


From source code
================

By default, nssbackup will be installed under "/usr/local" folder.

* Install python and python-gnome2 libraries, fuse-utils and pynotify.
  - probably it's already installed in your dist

* Walk into the same directory as this README file
* Run 'make'
* Run 'sudo make install'
* Run 'sudo nssbackupconfig'


Uninstalling
============

* If installed via apt: 'sudo apt-get remove nssbackup'. Else:

* Just type 'sudo make uninstall' in the source code folder
